-- Chelsea Beats Arsenal 2-1 in Premier League at Stamford Bridge
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2013-01-20T15:23:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-20/chelsea-beats-arsenal-2-1-in-premier-league-at-stamford-bridge.html
Chelsea beat London rival Arsenal
2-1 today to move to within 10 points of leader Manchester
United in English soccer’s Premier League.  Juan Mata  and  Frank Lampard , with a penalty kick, scored in
the opening 16 minutes for Chelsea at its Stamford Bridge
stadium, with Theo Walcott replying for Arsenal in the second
half.  Manchester United tops the standings with 55 points,
Manchester City has 51, with Chelsea on 45. Tottenham is five
points further back in fourth, while Arsenal remains on 34
points in sixth spot.   United is at Tottenham in today’s other game.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  